history.content:
"If I am on a waitlist for class A, but I am enrolled in class B (which has conflicting times), should I drop class B right now, or wait until I get off the waitlist for A?"

You will never get off the waitlist for A while you are enrolled in class B without some conflict override intervention from campus or the department (see @3869).  I can't answer the question of which class you should prioritize.

"Also, will I be unable to enroll in class A if I'm still enrolled in class B when I get off the waitlist for class A? "

You won't get off the waitlist for class A. See above.

If I am on a waitlist for class A, but I am enrolled in class B (which has conflicting times), should I drop class B right now, or wait until I get off the waitlist for A? Also, will I be unable to enroll in class A if I'm still enrolled in class B when I get off the waitlist for class A?
